{"id":"heth","term":"Heth","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Dread, a descendant of Canaan, and the ancestor of the Hittites (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:18\">Gen. 10:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 7:1\">Deut. 7:1</a>), who dwelt in the vicinity of Hebron (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:3\">Gen. 23:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:7\">7</a>). The Hittites were a Hamitic race. They are called “the sons of Heth” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:3\">Gen. 23:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:5\">5</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:7\">7</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:10\">10</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:16\">16</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:18\">18</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:20\">20</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 10:18","Deuteronomy 7:1","Genesis 23:3","Genesis 23:7","Genesis 23:5","Genesis 23:10","Genesis 23:16","Genesis 23:18","Genesis 23:20"]}